	  <item>
        <title>The Post/Page Template</title>
        <link>http://realjenius.com/design/page/</link>
		<author>R.J. Lorimer</author>
		<pubDate>2014-07-10T00:00:00+08:00</pubDate>
		<guid>http://realjenius.com/design/page/</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[
		   <p><em>Feeling Responsive</em> shows metadata by default. The default behaviour can be changed via <code class="highlighter-rouge">config.yml</code>. To show metadata at the end of a page/post just add the following to front matter:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><pre class="highlight"><code>show_meta: true
</code></pre>
</div>

<p>If you don’t want to show metadata, it’s simple again:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><pre class="highlight"><code>show_meta: false
</code></pre>
</div>

